fields.name: pJEx411a
fields.description:
__DNA 2.0 standard protein expression vector pJExpress411__

* ori: high copy, pUC-based
* promoter: T7 with lacO
* other features: lacI expression

Sequence is given from STOP to START

*Note*: fully annotated gbk file

fields.name: pJEx411b
fields.description:
__DNA 2.0 expression vector pJExpress411 version (b)__

In this version of the vector, we have removed a Esp3 IIS restriction site 68 bp downstream of the STOP codon (annotated in attached genbank file).

* **ori**: high copy, pUC-based
* **promoter**: T7 with lacO
* **other features**: lacI expression

Sequence is given from STOP to START

___Construction___

* **method**: Gibson assembly mutagenesis starting from Raik's rg2130_pJEx411
* **built by**: Samuel
* **initial construct**: sb0135

*Note*: partially annotated gbk

fields.name: pJEx411c
fields.description:
__cdog-modified DNA 2.0 expression vector pJExpress411 version (c)__

Built on pJEx411b, this version includes the RBS insulator casette of Endy et. al. to uncouple translation rate from RNA secondary structure effects. It also retains the deletion of the downstream Esp3 site which was introduced in pJEx411b

__Parameters__

* **ori**: high copy, pUC-based
* **promoter**: T7 with lacO
* **other features**: lacI expression, "leader RBS" and "leader peptide"

Sequence is given from STOP to START

__Construction__

* **method**: Gibson assembly with gBlock inserting the BCD2 highest-scoring insulation casette
* **by**: Shaima
* **initial construct**: 

*Note*: fully annotated gbk file

fields.name: pJ241
fields.description:
__undocumented DNA 2.0 expression vector__

A high-copy expression plasmid for E. coli, with non-specified (or non-existing) promoter. This plasmid backbone was sent to us by accident (instead of the ordered pJ421) but actually performs well. It is not documented on the DNA 2.0 web site.
Blast with the promoter region picks up some Cre recombination site from a random plasmid.

___Parameters__

* **ori**: high copy, pUC-based
* **promoter**: ??
* **other features**: KanR

Sequence is given from STOP to START

___Construction___

* delivered with gene synthesis of sb0002 and sb0004

fields.name: pJEx824
fields.description:

Sequence is given from STOP to START

___Construction___

fields.name: pJ603a
fields.description:
__DNA 2.0 mammalian expression vector pJ603 version (a)__

Mammalian vector for transient overexpression. 

The different pJ603 versions (a - c) only differ in their C-terminal cloning scar. pJ603a is the older version which uses a `TAA` STOP codon, followed by a XhoI restriction site:

> insert-TAA-CTCGAGAA-constant`

* **ori**: SV40 
* **bacterial ori**: high copy, pUC-based
* **promoter**: CMV
* **other features**: Neomycin and (bacterial) Ampicilin resistance

Sequence is given from STOP to START

__Construction__

delivered with DNA 2.0 gene synthesis of Raik's hiFRET constructs rg2100 - rg2102

fields.name: pJ603b
fields.description:
__DNA 2.0 mammalian expression vector pJ603 version (b)__

Mammalian vector for transient overexpression. 

The different pJ603 versions (a - c) only differ in their C-terminal cloning scar. pJ603b uses a `TAA` STOP codon **without** Xho restriction site. This means it has a 8 bp  `CTCGAGAA` deletion with respect to pJ603a:

> insert-TAA-constant

* **ori**: SV40 
* **bacterial ori**: high copy, pUC-based
* **promoter**: CMV
* **other features**: Neomycin and (bacterial) Ampicilin resistance

Sequence is given from STOP to START

__Construction__

delivered with DNA 2.0 gene synthesis of Raik's hiFRET constructs rg2110 - rg2113

fields.name: pJ603c
fields.description:
__DNA 2.0 mammalian expression vector pJ603 version (c)__

Mammalian vector for transient overexpression. 

The different pJ603 versions (a - c) only differ in their C-terminal cloning scar. pJ603c is the same as pJ603a but uses a `TGA` STOP codon (followed by a Xho restriction site):

> insert-TGA-CTCGAGAA-constant-backbone

* **ori**: SV40 
* **bacterial ori**: high copy, pUC-based
* **promoter**: CMV
* **other features**: Neomycin and (bacterial) Ampicilin resistance

Sequence is given from STOP to START

__Construction__

delivered with DNA 2.0 gene synthesis of Raik's unimolecular hiFRET constructs rg2130 - rg2135

fields.name: pJ609a
fields.description:
__DNA 2.0 mammalian expression vector pJ609 version (a)__

Mammalian vector for transient overexpression. This is the older version of the pJ609 vector that contains a XhoI cloning site after the TAA STOP:

> insert-TAA-CTCGAGAA-constant

* **ori**: SV40 
* **bacterial ori**: high copy, pUC-based
* **promoter**: CMV
* **other features**: Puromycin and (bacterial) Ampicilin resistance

Sequence is given from STOP to START

__Construction__

delivered with DNA 2.0 gene synthesis of Raik's hiFRET constructs rg2103 - rg2105

fields.name: pJ609b
fields.description:
__DNA 2.0 mammalian expression vector pJ609 version (b)__

Mammalian vector for transient overexpression. This is a more recent version of the pJ609 vector which is lacking the XhoI cloning site after the TAA STOP:

> insert-TAA-constant

* **ori**: SV40 
* **bacterial ori**: high copy, pUC-based
* **promoter**: CMV
* **other features**: Puromycin and (bacterial) Ampicilin resistance

Sequence is given from STOP to START

__Construction__

delivered with DNA 2.0 gene synthesis of Raik's hiFRET constructs rg2114 - rg2115
